Loads a value from the pointer.

`load` takes an [`Ordering`](enum.Ordering.html "enum std::sync::atomic::Ordering") argument which describes the memory ordering of this operation. Possible values are [`SeqCst`](about:blank/enum.Ordering.html#variant.SeqCst "variant std::sync::atomic::Ordering::SeqCst"), [`Acquire`](about:blank/enum.Ordering.html#variant.Acquire "variant std::sync::atomic::Ordering::Acquire") and [`Relaxed`](about:blank/enum.Ordering.html#variant.Relaxed "variant std::sync::atomic::Ordering::Relaxed").

